	<h2>
	About Kate
	</h2>

	<p>
	Kate Lyster is a designer and entrepreneur from Sandpoint, Idaho. She grew up enjoying all that this magnificent region offers—skiing, hiking, camping, and mountain biking—along with every activity available on Lake Pend Oreille, the jewel of Northern Idaho.
	</p>

	<p>
	Kate spent her youth on an off-grid ranch in the Selkirk Mountains where she learned to see and appreciate nature in its fullest. She later apprenticed at her aunt’s New York design showroom gaining a wealth of experience about space, feel and design. For more than 2 decades, Kate has integrated these seemingly disparate experiences into thoughtful, dynamic design sensibility—equally suited to an urban loft and an off-grid cabin.
	</p>

	<p>
	Grounded in the wild textures of Sandpoint and shaped by a lifelong devotion to thoughtful design, Kate has always been drawn to the quiet dialogue between nature and the built environment. As founder of Base Camp Design, her work has long reflected an appreciation for authenticity, craftsmanship, and the understated luxury of natural materials.
	</p>

	<p>
	Elliott Cole Home emerged as a natural extension of that vision—a response to the need for a modern, design-forward furniture and lifestyle showroom that reflects the mountain and lake culture of North Idaho. What Kate couldn’t find elsewhere, she created: a space where elevated design, artisan craft, and the warmth of lived experience converge.
	</p>

	<p>
	Through her relationships with regional makers and her instinct for meaningful interiors, Kate curates collections and environments that feel soulful, rooted, and timeless. Whether shaping a home or building a brand, she approaches each project with an artist’s eye and a storyteller’s heart, weaving together the textures, tones, and moments that define a life well lived.
	</p>
